<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/466101-is-this-a-true-story">Is this a true story?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_466101'><a id="like_count_community_question_466101" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/466101?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">2 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F178796.The_Good_Women_of_China">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/466101-is-this-a-true-story">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/466101-is-this-a-true-story">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/20738920-orinoco-womble-tidy-bag-and-all"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1406361683i/20738920._UX100_CR0,18,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/20738920-orinoco-womble-tidy-bag-and-all">Orinoco Womble (tidy bag and all)</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It&apos;s not a &quot;story&quot; in the novel/autobiography sense, but rather a collection of anecdotes taken from the author&apos;s experience as a radio journalist in <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It's not a "story" in the novel/autobiography sense, but rather a collection of anecdotes taken from the author's experience as a radio journalist in China during the "opening up" years of Deng Xiaoping. The unifying thread is the author's own journey in discovering more about the millions of anonymous lives around her.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

