<div id="review_305769221" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/305769221" />
    <a title="Missy J" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7406091-missy-j"><img alt="Missy J" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1481102743p2/7406091.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/305769221?book_show_action=true">Apr 03, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Missy J" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Missy J" href="/user/show/7406091-missy-j">Missy J</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7406091-missy-j?shelf=asia-related">asia-related</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7406091-missy-j?shelf=china-related">china-related</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7406091-missy-j?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7406091-missy-j?shelf=biography">biography</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7406091-missy-j?shelf=2012-books">2012-books</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer305769221" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15877174619541869133">If I could, I would give this book 4.5*!<br/><br/>Xinran is a Chinese journalist, who left China in 1997 in order to publish this book. After reading this book, I can understand why. &quot;The Good Women of China&quot; contains 15 stories, among them &quot;The Guomindang General&apos;s Daughter,&quot; &quot;The Woman Whose Father Does Not Know Her,&quot; &quot;The Fashionable Woman&quot; and &quot;The Women of Shouting Hill&quot; (my favorite stories), which tell of unimaginable sufferings and abuses in the hands of husbands, fathers, strangers and government</span>
  <span id="freeText15877174619541869133" style="display:none">If I could, I would give this book 4.5*!<br /><br />Xinran is a Chinese journalist, who left China in 1997 in order to publish this book. After reading this book, I can understand why. "The Good Women of China" contains 15 stories, among them "The Guomindang General's Daughter," "The Woman Whose Father Does Not Know Her," "The Fashionable Woman" and "The Women of Shouting Hill" (my favorite stories), which tell of unimaginable sufferings and abuses in the hands of husbands, fathers, strangers and government officials. The Party couldn't approve this book and the voices of these women would never have been heard. These stories are depressing and heartbreaking. This book taught me much about China during the 60s till the 90s, especially about the abuses during the Cultural Revolution. It comes as no surprise that a lot of people are still traumatized by these events. </span>
  <a data-text-id="15877174619541869133" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


